Unrestrained logging, an increase in wildfire frequency, an increase in road construction around known habitat have all contributed to the population decline since the 1980s. There have also been a number of major organizational changes which have had the effect of diluting, if not deleting, relevant scientific expertise within government departments nominally responsible for the environmental health of the Central Highlands forests.



